      "id": "GENUS_MICROCARBO",
      "name": "Microcarbo",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "Pygmy cormorants — small, long-tailed cormorants of freshwater lakes and rivers in Africa, southern Asia, and Australasia. The smallest members of the cormorant family, they have proportionally longer tails and shorter bills than their larger relatives. Pygmy cormorants are highly gregarious, often nesting in mixed colonies with herons and ibises, and they employ a cooperative feeding strategy where groups drive fish into shallows before diving.",
