      "id": "GENUS_POIKILOCARBO",
      "name": "Poikilocarbo",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "Red-legged cormorant — a monotypic genus found along the Pacific coast of South America from northern Peru to Tierra del Fuego. Easily distinguished from all other cormorants by its vivid coral-red legs and feet, which contrast sharply with its grey-blue plumage and orange throat patch. The red-legged cormorant is a specialist of exposed rocky shores and strong tidal currents, where it forages in the surf zone among breaking waves.",
