      "name": "Urile",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "North Pacific cormorants — a genus of four species that breed on the cold coasts and islands of the northern Pacific Rim, from Japan and Kamchatka across the Aleutians to western North America. They have distinctive bare facial skin patterns and, in most species, a bright blue or purple gape. One species, the spectacled cormorant, is the only cormorant to have gone extinct in historical times, vanishing from the Commander Islands around 1850.",
