      "id": "GENUS_GULOSUS",
      "name": "Gulosus",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "European shag — a monotypic genus separated from Phalacrocorax by molecular studies, restricted to the temperate and boreal coastal waters of Europe and North Africa. The European shag is distinguished from the great cormorant by its smaller size, more slender build, iridescent green-black plumage, and a distinctive forward-curling crest in breeding plumage. Unlike the great cormorant, it is strictly a marine species that rarely if ever ventures onto fresh water.",
