      "id": "GENUS_NANNOPTERUM",
      "name": "Nannopterum",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "American cormorants — a genus of three species restricted to the Americas, including the only flightless cormorant in the world. These cormorants have undergone rapid evolutionary diversification in the New World, from the Galápagos flightless cormorant to the widespread double-crested and neotropic cormorants. The genus was long lumped into Phalacrocorax but molecular studies confirm its distinctness, with the flightless cormorant representing an extreme adaptation to an island environment without terrestrial predators.",
      "lineage": "American Cormorants",
      "children": [
